The paper discusses the design of secure and reliable wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of network security and information theory. The use of random graphs and pairwise key predistribution schemes is a common technique in this area, which suggests the paper may belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also analyzes the strength of connectivity of the network, which involves graph theory and algorithms, indicating that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the security implications of the network design, which suggests it may belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper provides simulations to demonstrate the usefulness of the results, which suggests it may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
